modules.description: Handles asynchronous I/O operations such as reading from and writing to network sockets, with support for non-blocking event loops. Operates on file descriptors, buffers, and asynchronous promises. Used to implement real-time communication protocols and handle concurrent network requests efficiently.

Provides route handling and registration for asynchronous HTTP endpoints. Works with route lists and handler functions defined using a custom syntax. Used to build dynamic web services with non-blocking I/O operations.
